{
  "doc_id": "40643",
  "text": "The readability of written material should not exceed the reading age of 12 years old and for US and UK populations ideally be aimed at eighth grade (13-14 years old) and grades 5-6 (10-11 years old), respectively [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Previous investigations of dental practice leaflets readability have found leaflets to be difficult to read with a mean Flesch Reading Ease level ranging between 55.2 (SD 12.5) and 72.19 (SD 4.75) [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Similarly, UK hospital patient information leaflets have been assessed to have a mean Flesch-Kincaid reading grade of 7.8 and deemed to exceed the comprehension of readers [CITATION_5] .",
